# {{.Name}} ({{.Type}})

{{ .Description | trimspace }}

This resource manages only the `state` of an existing Microsoft-managed forwarding policy link attached to a Microsoft Entra Global Secure Access forwarding profile.

## Microsoft Documentation

- [What is Global Secure Access?](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/entra/global-secure-access/overview-what-is-global-secure-access)
- [Traffic forwarding profiles](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/entra/global-secure-access/concept-traffic-forwarding)
- [Internet Access](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/entra/global-secure-access/concept-internet-access)
- [Update forwardingPolicyLink](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/networkaccess-forwardingpolicylink-update?view=graph-rest-beta)

## Microsoft Graph API

This resource uses Microsoft Graph beta `/networkAccess/forwardingProfiles/{forwardingProfileId}/policies/{policyLinkId}`.

Create and update both send `PATCH` because Microsoft creates the forwarding profile policy links. Delete is a remote no-op and removes only Terraform state so Terraform does not delete Microsoft-managed links.

## Microsoft Graph API Permissions

The following client `application` permissions are needed in order to use this {{.Type | lower}}:

**Required:**
- `NetworkAccess.Read.All`
- `NetworkAccess.ReadWrite.All`

**Optional:**
- `None` `[N/A]`

## Behavior Notes

- `policy_link_id` is distinct from the linked `policy_id`.
- This resource should be used for adopted Microsoft-managed policy links, such as the Internet Access `Default Acquire` link.
- Destroy does not delete the Graph object. Re-apply can adopt the same link again.

